title: Enums for log levels. See IQConnect Logging

javaEnums.title: Admin log entries are non-data and non-request related log entries. Enabled by default.
L1Data log entries consists of all data transferred over the Level 1 Port.
L1Request log entries consists of all requests received from client apps on the Level 1 Port.
L1System log entries consists of all system messages received from and sent to the client on the Level 1 Port.
L1Error log entries consists of all errors sent to the client on the Level 1 Port.
L2Data log entries consists of all data transferred over the Level 2 Port.
L2Request log entries consists of all requests received from client apps on the Level 2 Port.
L2System log entries consists of all system messages received from and sent to the client on the Level 2 Port.
L2Error log entries consists of all errors sent to the client on the Level 2 Port.
LookupData log entries consists of all data transferred over the Lookup Port.
LookupRequest log entries consists of all requests received from client apps on the Lookup Port.
LookupError log entries consists of all errors sent to the client on the Lookup Port.
Information logging enables basic information, such as username and product id to be logged to the file. Enabled by default.
Debug logs enable more granular logging to aid in troubleshooting issues.
Connectivity log entries are related to the connection/reconnection between IQConnect and the server. Enabled by default.
